fcoclavero.message: Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jSwingRipples/jswingripples
Fixed search errors
Added clear search button to search panel.
REmoved unused import.
Removed unnecessary highlights.
Added search results column in table view.
Added total search hits to table view.

Refactoring.

- Renamed searchHits method to hitPercentage.
- Updated render other column docs.
Removed deprecated  method indexProject.

Updated highlight color scale.

- Scale is based on difference between the maximum and minimum frequency of the searched term in each file.
- Search results are now stored in a HashMap with the filename as key and appearance frequency as value.
No directory error fixed.
Indexes are now saved on user dir.
Changed highlight colors.
Completed docs.
Refresh table after search.
Max hits tweaks.
Initial highlight implementation.
Optional indexing from EIG.
Integrated search to search menu.
Indexer class refactoring. It now closes the IndexWriter after indexing the project.
Files are now indexed upon project analysis.
Minor refactoring to searcher class.
Indexer now indexes valid files only. Only java files considered for now.
Added file filter for manageable files.

File filters.

- Added abstract method to create file filters based on file extension.
- Implemented a .java extension filter.
Indexer now indexes subdirectories.

Indexer and Searcher class now implement a singleton pattern.
The indexProject method now receives a JavaProject object.
JavaProject now a field. Facilitates index creation.
Minor refactoring.
Created StartSearchAction class to separate search behaviour from  UI implementation.

Refactoring

- Moved NewSearchMenu to search package
- Optimized NewSearchMenu imports
- Optimized JSwingRipplesApplication imports
- Reverted changes to the addProject method in the JavaProjectModel class causing test failures.
Updated iml
Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/search_menu' into search_dev

Merge branch 'lucene_integration' into search_dev

Search development integration.
Moved max hits constants from Searcher class to LuceneConstants class.
Added index directory path to lucene constants.
Minor refactoring.

Project indexing

- Project indices are now created from the JavaProject class instead of the EIG representation.

Constants

- Added class containing constants used throughout the search process.
- Refactored Searcher and Indexer to use the newly defined constants.
Completed javadocs for the search classes.
Minor refactoring to Searcher class.
Optimized searcher imports.

Search Class.

- Initial implementation of the search class, now refactored to fit the new lucene version.
- Minor refactoring to Searcher class.
Indexer class refactoring to match new Lucene version.
Changed Lucene version to 3.6.2 for ease of use.
Changed Lucene version to latest (6.0.0)
Changed Lucene dependency version in pom.xml
Initial Lucene indexer implementation.
Added lucene search library dependency to pom.xml

cguzmanp.body:
## Initialization

Se ha de crear un plug-in de Eclipse desde el cual sea posible lanzar la aplicación.

## Concept Location

Plug-in, eclipse, launch.

## Impact Analysis

Ninguna clase de JSwingRipples se verá afectada, ya que esto corresponde a la creación de un plug-in aparte.

## Prefactoring

Creación de un repositorio para la creación del plug-in.

## Actualization

- Se instala software para el desarrollo de plug-ins para Eclipse (PDE)
- Se crea un nuevo menú y botón de selección para la UI de Eclipse, con una pequeña ventana de pop-up como placeholder de la funcionalidad.
- La funcionalidad es agregada, en donde luego de hacer click en el botón en la barra de herramientas, o clickear "Open JSwingRipples" en el menú "JSwingRipples" en la barra menú, se abré la aplicación en su estado inicial.
- Se modifica de forma de cambiar el nombre y tooltips de algunos menús.

## PostFactoring

- Se descargan un par de .jar que son necesarios para el funcionamiento correcto del código creado.

## Conclusion

Una vez instalado el plug-in, el usuario es capaz de abrir la aplicación JSwingRipples desde la interfaz de Eclipse.

- Descripción: Desarrollar plug-in que permita abrir la aplicación desde Eclipse.
- Fuente: Analista.

- Estabilidad: Intransable.
